TWO
suspects tried to bribe and SIU detective. The two
suspects between the ages of 44 and 34 were arrested by Hawks serious
corruption members on Wednesday. The pair
reportedly tried to bribe the SIU detective in order to exclude the portion of
the report that recommended that their company be charged criminally. Hawks
spokesperson Brigadier Hangwani Mulaudzi said the finding was that the company
should pay back R3 million and face criminal charges for a tender that was not
serviced yet they submitted documents to the Mopani Municipality for payments. The
suspects allegedly tried to bribe him with a R300 000 which led to their
immediate arrest. The
National Head of the DPCI Lieutenant General Godfrey Lebeya praised both teams
for collaborating in the arrest of the two suspects. Meanwhile,
the Head of the SIU National Advocate Any Mothibi as also welcomed the arrest
of the criminals and commended the SIU investigator who demonstrated that SIU
investigators put integrity at the centre of their work. The
suspects are expected to appear at the Polokwane Magistrate court on charges of
corruption. 